---
import BaseLayout from '../../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Reader Orientation Map" description="A simple first route-map for reading Vaelinya.">
  <section class="page-section">
    <p class="eyebrow">Artefacts · Maps</p>
    <h1>Reader orientation map</h1>
    <p class="lede">This is the first simple map for entering Vaelinya: begin with Lina, then move outward into world, language, and artefacts.</p>

    <article class="visual-callout visual-callout-world">
      <div class="visual-callout-mark" aria-hidden="true"><span>↔</span></div>
      <div class="visual-callout-copy">
        <p class="eyebrow">Text map</p>
        <h2>One clear first route</h2>
        <p>Read Lina first. Then follow the Rim, the Rimaeri, the Warm Remembering, and the symbols that help the stories connect.</p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="panel">
      <p class="eyebrow">Route</p>
      <h2>First reading path</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Lina’s eight stories</strong> — the clearest first story path.</li>
        <li><strong>The Rim</strong> — the edge-place and borderland where Vaelinya begins to open.</li>
        <li><strong>The Rimaeri</strong> — the people of the Rim.</li>
        <li><strong>The Warm Remembering</strong> — a cultural thread of care, continuity, and shared remembrance.</li>
        <li><strong>NAVAN</strong> — the first public symbol-word: Remember.</li>
      </ol>
      <p>This page is intentionally text-first so the map remains usable without sight, image loading, or colour.</p>
    </article>

    <div class="link-list" aria-label="Reader orientation links">
      <a href="/read/lina/">Start with Lina’s stories</a>
      <a href="/world/the-rim/">Open The Rim</a>
      <a href="/world/rimaeri/">Meet the Rimaeri</a>
      <a href="/world/the-warm-remembering/">Follow the Warm Remembering</a>
      <a href="/artefacts/symbols/navan/">Open the NAVAN symbol</a>
    </div>

    <p><a class="button secondary" href="/artefacts/maps/">Back to maps</a></p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
